# Accessibility Rules

- Ensure semantic HTML tags are used for their intended purpose.
- Ensure all interactive elements have visible focus states.
- Ensure all CTA links and buttons are accessible (e.g., proper aria-labels if needed, high contrast).
- Follow WCAG guidelines for color contrast.
- Ensure proper form labels and structural markup.
